@node "Bugs" "Bugs         "
@next "Future"
@prev "Author"

 Known (very minor...) bugs
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

 NewHomer_DATA.lha file:

 - the newhomer.conf file that comes with this archive does NOT use all the
   samples into the archive!!!! it is an error, but it was stated into the
   config file itself that many samples where missing. However, for those
   of you that never read docs, I've put a good one into the main archive
   and changed the installer accordingly, too.
 - There is at least ONE sample "evilhomer.wav" that differs from the
   configuration file... please change either one to fix it.

 Main program, a bug fixed and coming from an OS function (AGA only systems):

 - A couple of AGA-only people :) wrote me telling that NewHomer couldn't
   show the animation. I tried with an AGA/ECS screen and had no problems,
   so I removed Cgx and the same bug appeared. So I've discovered that the
   funcion gfx.lib/BitMapScale() which is used to zoom the animation is
   bugged IF NO ZOOM on the x axis occurs. It is bugged ONLY on ECS/AGA
   screens :( WITHOUT CyberGfx/Picasso96 installed... when it won't zoom
   on the x axis the resulting bitmap is pure garbage. I had to read some
   docs to get back to those old funny assembler-only days :)) and put a
   y zooming blitter routine. I repeat this is _ONLY_ activated on AGA/ECS
   screens WITHOUT Cgx/P96 active AND IF ScaleFactorX is equal to 100!!
   If you are using a blitter-killer tool like FBlit, my routine will
   still work, but maybe slower than with FBlit os-patched routines (oh
   gee, this won't ever be noticed, unless you put Homer window to have
   a ScaleFactor of 1000 on Y and 100 on X... :)). To fix this I've added
   a tooltype called "FBLIT", if you set this OS routine BltBitMap() will
   be used instead of custom blitter code... Repeat again: ONLY USED when
   under AGA/ECS WITHOUT Cgx/P96 and ScaleFactorX == 100. In all the other
   cases BitMapScale() (DAMN BUGGY!!!) is used, so no FBlit slowdowns
   occur. See also @{"Configuration" link "Configuration" 0}

 - No other bugs at the moment... but they keep getting out from time to
   time... ;)

 For the list of (possibly) removed bugs, please see @{"history" link "History" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Future" "Future          "
@next "Thanks"
@prev "Bugs"

 Future
 ~~~~~~

 This version (1.8) will PROBABLY be the last one. Unless someone creates:

   1) A different (and possibly better) animation of Homer
   2) An animation of a different character (and possibly some samples for it).

 OR:

 - Some new bug appear and has to be fixed.

 As I already said somewhere in this doc, you can change the animation in
 any way you like, thus it is possible to have a 'Bart', 'Lisa', 'Marge',
 a 'GrandPa' and so on :). The big limitation now is that the position of
 the eyes must be respected, it can't be changed, so I'd say that the
 dimensions of a frame must be the same of Homer too (currently they are 26x32
 pixels wide).
@endnode

