@node "History" "History"
@prev "Thanks"

 History
 ~~~~~~~

 V 0.9  - Internal release... some enforcer hits here and there

 V 1.0  - First Aminet Release, Easter 2001. Removed all the enforcer hits.

 V 1.1  - (27/5/2001)

          Second Aminet update, many bugs fixed, some enhancements

          - 16 bit samples weren't recognized by the player... I thought
            that data was converted to 8 bit, but reading some docs I found
            the existance of two more tags ;) to handle sound data with a
            resolution deeper than 8 bits.
            Only works with a sound.datatype able to cope with this (as far
            as I know only the v41sound.datatype does).
          - Fixed a bug of V1.0 that made the program unusable under AGA.
          - Fixed the config parser.

 v 1.2  - (28/6/2001)

          Third update. Some bugs fixed, one addition.

          - WindowXPos and YPos didn't get used to put window starting
            position... stupid! now it has been fixed.
          - now you can choose any name you want for the tooltypes (even
            with quotes or spaces, even if AmigaOs doesn't suggest to use
            spaces in file names).
          - the dictionary window (when you press the help key ;), won't
            overlap the main window when this latter is near the right
            screen border.
          - the routine that draws the eyes could have erased wrong part of
            picture when Homer changed his mood. This doesn't happen
            anymore.
          - Fixed some other rare (and very minor) bugs...


 v 1.3  - (24/7/2001)

          Fourth update. Major bug fixes, a couple really stupid.

          - the eyes will follow the mouse using a decent calculation now,
            basic vector math used :))
          - The player task was created/destroyed each time. Not a real
            bug, but now it is created once at the beginning thus sparing
            some fragmentation to ram..:))
          - There was a bug with audio channel allocation: allocation of NO
            channels could happen under some circumstances. Both the player
            and the maintask entered this way in an endless loop, causing
            obviously troubles.
          - There was a "DeleteMsgPort()" on a NON EXISTANT port (ie it was
            performed twice even on a copy of it). This happenned at exit
            of the program and every time it was iconificated... I think
            that this was causing the biggest stability troubles.
          - ScaleFactorX was put to 100% by default instead of 0% (thus not
            allowing the config routine to put it to the same value of
            ScaleFactor). If you used the old homer.conf file (from Homer
            1.5/1.6) and had a scale factor greater than 100%, it would
            have scaled just on the y axis (making a too slim Homer, he has
            been his whole life a "obese man trapped inside a fat man's
            body" don't forget it! :)


 v 1.4  - (31/7/2001)

          - Cgx lib. was required even if not used. Fixed. Thanks to
            "Michał D±browski" (should appear some polish character there?
            =)) for reporting. He reported also another fast bug: paths
            with more than one slash char (/) ie with a depth of more than
            root volume (:) and a dir didn't work. I think this was the
            most stupid bug of all :(
          - Added a title and a close gadget to the help window
          - The installer has a bug with the function "AskChoice", now I
            have found a workaround to it, and also added another option to
            NewHomer installer.
          - Also bumped installer version to an up-to-date one.
          - Improved a bit this guide file.

---------- some holydays here  :) --------

 v 1.5 - (10/8/2001 my birthday...)
          - Michael Debrowski signalled another error with the config.file,
            the sample "evilhomer.wav" was named "evlhomer.wav"... duh!
          - WinX and WinY parameter were totally ignored. Now will be igno-
            red only if they are too small (as stated into the config
            file).
          - Now if the window width is too small for the three gadgets it
            must have, some space will be left in order to still be able to
            use the drag bar. Should have done this even before... but
            again, due to the QUICK nature of NewHomer release, it left
            space just for the three gadgets... now will use 3+8/9 of a
            gadget for the window title bar.
          - Added a fix in the installer for the config file that came with
            "NewHomer_DATA.lha" file with the american samples. That file
            was set to use JUST a bunch of samples, many were missing (and
            it must have been VERY VERY disappointing for those who
            downloaded those 2.7 megabytes of stuff...)
          - Added an italian .readme ;) but I don't think there's need for
            this guide...
          - But thanks to "Ital 3.01" now there's an italian guide too :)

 v 1.6 - (16/08/2001)

          - Thanks to John Marchant's bugreport, I was able to discover a
            sort of bug into the graphics/BitMapScale() function. When the
            ratio of width resizing is 1:1 AND width is an odd number, this
            function returns JUNK into the destination bitmap (thus Homer
            was not much enjoyable on AGA/ECS only systems). Now I've put
            a custom assembly routine that replaces the os one only in that
            case. Damn OS bugs!!
            This bug WON'T happen in presence of cybergraphics.library (!!)
            even on an AGA screen, so I didn't noticed it before. If you
            used a different ScaleFactorX (eg 200%) it would have NOT
            happenned too... mysteries of Amiga ROMs...
          - While solving this problem, I've discovered another 'hidden'
            with the picture-swap routine (it wouldn't have caused any
            problems before, but anyway now it is fixed).
          - Cleaned up some parts of the code and added the possibility to
            resize the window on the fly.
          - Added the "FBLIT" tooltype, for those who hate Amiga's Blitter.
          - Added the "FollowMouse" option, for those who like to keep the
            window of NewHomer right in the middle of the screen.
          - Fixed this doc to work better under 640*Y 'topaz.8' screens,
            plus removed/fixed a couple of errors.
          - Also, fixed a misbehaviour with the "ManyDoh" option: it worked,
            but, in case of miss (ie don't continue to say d'oh but instead
            do something else), the "d'oh" was reinserted in the weighted
            choice; thus, depending also on the values used, it could have
            hapenned that Homer had said A LOT of "d'oh"s :))
          - Fixed an error with the 'Cancel' button when NO audio.channel
            where free: didn't freed some ram.

 v 1.7 - (19/09/2001 - 16/03/03)

         -  This version laid abandoned on my HD... I can't remember if there
            where any bugs fixed or what else.
         -  Now it has been recompiled with GCC (StormC4). The executable is a
            bit longer, I don't think anyone will care though.
         -  It is the stablest version: I can't make it crash in any way.

         -  Fixed such a silly bug I didn't notice (I probably had "ham"
            slices on my eyes...). Now the eyes of Homer WILL follow the
            mouse pointer in a realistic way. I mistook a value for the square
            root function... d'oh!!!

         -  Added a configuration option: AudioVolume to set the audio output
            volume (see enhancements).

 v 1.8 - (30/03/03 funny date =))

         -  Found a dead routine (!): error messages were not displayed anymore
            and this is bad, and happenned after the 2 years of black-out
            (have a look at the dates in V1.7).

         -  Now Homer blinks as old Homer 1.6 did.
         -  Eyes won't be updated unless stricly necessary, removes flicker.
         -  Forgot to clip AudioVolume if (badly!) put to values higher than
            64.
         -  Fixed some RISKY code here and there (as much as I could remember).
         -  Fixed a bit the guide files (dates and versions here and there).
         -  Fixed also italian guide (there was not too much "italian language"
            in it, since I had it translated from the english doc.

         -  Fixed some frames into the animation, having a pixel overlapping
            with an eye position.
         -  Installer updated to cope with these changes.

         -  Added audio channel side allocation according to window position.
            If the correct channels are not free, NewHomer tries to allocate the
            first one it finds.

         -  Added a couple of key controls for the maniacs...

 v 1.81  - (02/04/03 another funny date =)) - NOT RELEASED TO THE PUBLIC -

         -  Now Homer repeats also d'ohs not only belches. Also, since those
            "maniac" key bindings have been added, there will be MIDDLE mouse
            button to force Homer talking, from the mouse, and return/enter
            from the keyboard) or wait Homer to start talking by himself.
            I think this way things make (a very little) more sense.
         -  Slightly changed main icon and anim
         -  Found a bug into the sample replayer. I noticed somebody uploaded
            a 'corrected' bunch of samples, so I thought:

            1) someone is still using NewHomer
            2) the player could still have unnoticed bugs.

            Well, it was ONLY BY CHANCE that I discovered a bug that prevented
            STEREO samples (both 8 or 16 bits) from working. Now those samples
            are also scaled down to 8 bits mono and played back on the fly.
            Before, this only worked with mono 16 bits samples.

            Now, the trouble with NH_Data was actually another...!
            NewHomerDATA samples were mostly coming from the old Homer 1.6...
            bad but true I discovered that due to a strange header, such files
            are NOT recognized by standard v44 datatypes, while they are
            recognized, for example, by v41 ones. I couldn't check wether they
            work or not with v40 or v39, if there's someone that can do this
            test...

 v 1.82 - (05/04/03 let's stop with it...) - INTERNAL -

         -  Reworked some code... I notice AmigaOS has problems when Timer IO
            requests are reused in a burst way.
         -  Fixed a stupid bug occurring in EVERY version from 1.7: people
            without "titlebar.image" class were unable to open Homer's window:
            that was due to porting under GCC, I had mischanged a constant
            value to "cls" instead of "class". Didn't noticed this since I use
            VisualPrefs and have the tbi class installed. Thanks to Allan
            Rasmussen for reporting the problem.
         -  Added some (just two actually :)) more error messages if something
            goes wrong during the startup.

 v 1.83  - (06/04/03) - INTERNAL -

         -  Heavily CHANGED Main Program <-> Player loop code. For the moment
            the only side effect is that the code is MUCH clearer, and the
            executable is about 1k shorter ;)
         -  Sample at exit is now played by homer with current mood.
         -  Fixed a chance of division by zero (with a bad configuration file).
         -  Added "[StartSample]","[EndSamples]" and "ActivateWindow" options
         -  "NoExitSample" was NOT working...! Dunno why, I'm sure in the old
            -pre crash- sources I used it... sorry guys.
         -  I tried to destroy my keyboard in testing worst situations for
            NH... no crashes, no hits, nothing, it is just working after the
            changes, and I hope it will do so yet for long.

 v 1.84 RC 1 - (07/04/03)

         -  V1.84 will be the FIRST RC version (release candidate...). No more
            stupid statements about the final version.
         -  Added the PUBSCREEN tooltype.
         -  Fixed the installer... "FBLIT" tooltype was NOT setted at all!!
         -  "timer.device" remained allocated during iconification. Not a bug
            but simply it kept a resource busy without using it.

 v 1.85 RC 2 - (09/04/03)

         -  AS I SAID BEFORE, I'm still "recovering" the sources... I looked
            here and there, and found some more (old) quirks to the code.
         -  SadMood and AngryMood had swapped values in the config file.
         -  Added italian installer plus an option to it.
         -  DoPleasure option DIDN'T WORK, and probably NEVER DID... now I've
            reactivated it in a way "compatible" to the previous one.
         -  Added "[(de)iconifysamples]" and "IconifyMood" options. Guess what
            are they for?
         -  Added "SaveMem" option, for those of you who need every k of ram.
            Also added a different animation (a bit worse), that might let you
            spare about 3k of ram for less powerful Amigas.
         -  Added "StartSampleMood"; it can be =5 for "belch" and =6 ("d'oh").
         -  Fixed this doc: "FinalMood" can now be one of "belch" or "d'oh".
         -  The notification for "ENV:Screenmode.prefs" file was allocated even
            when opening on a non Worbench 'like' screen. This would have
            caused NH to iconify if the wb screen changed.
         -  NewHomer tried to allocate INSTANTLY the appicon when it was forced
            to iconify by a screenmode change. This could cause troubles and
            leave the program in a "zombie" state. Now NH waits 5 seconds then
            tries to put on the appicon for two more seconds before failing
            and quitting.
            If ya need more than 5 secs, you have to close NH or buy a faster
            Amiga (hint: buy a PC with WinUAE).
         -  Improved code here and there. In particular I signal the "Follow-
            Mouse" option: now bitmap flipping performs a bit better (not
            that faster, but on slower Amiga could be noticeable) and Homer
            will follow the mouse even while he is speaking... try to believe it ;).
            A good example when you spare some CPU cycles to be able to waste them
            some time later...!! :)).

 v 1.86 RC 3 - (21/04/03)

         -  Fixed a bug introduced with V1.85: inserted some code into a wrong
            "if" condition. Would have not correctly updated the window when
            Homer started (or deiconified) looking towards right.
            Worked ok with "SaveMem" parameter on. But this defaulted to 0...!
            Sorry for this stupid bug. Since no bugreports came to me, I deduce
            that most of you are using NH with the "LookLeft" parameter ON and
            the "FolloMouse" probably OFF...!
         -  Used WaitBlit() instead of custom assembly code. Only applies to
            people with AGA only, no FBLIT tooltype set, and no XZoomed anim.

  v 1.87 RC 4 - (25/04/03)

         -  Made NewHomer totally "case compliant" (ie now NewHomer should work
            also on case sensitive file systems).
            Please use the updated configuration file if u want to use NewHomer
            on such devices.
         -  Pleasure moods would have vanished in most of the cases due to an
            inverted if conditions... duh!
         -  Cleared some code misbehaving under a bad configuration file.
         -  Changed puddle size for memory pools.
         -  Fixed a data structure. Changed sample name parser. Now should be
            quite more resistant to VERY bad config names.
@endnode
